        myDickENG.Add("8_1111","You decide to go left. Going to the left, you notice on the floor a map of this place at one of the skeletons in your hands, you see on the map that the road led to the crocodile pond to the right, it’s good that you didn’t go there, the crocodiles have a bad taste, they say. You continued to move deep into these dungeons, while reading the map, suddenly you notice a coin icon on the map. You begin to think over the route in order to get to this treasured coin. Suddenly, you hear noises behind, you know their source. It's time to move. It’s good that they don’t have a card, at least you hope so. Bypassing all kinds of traps, which are also kindly indicated on the map, you come closer to the coin. And here you are. You got out to a large cave in which a whole frigate would fit. Moreover, this place was once inhabited, judging by the wooden houses here and there. Suddenly you see that the windows in one of the decrepit houses are burning. You go, pushing yourself, to this house, to which, by the way, the map also leads. After a short time scrambling on wet stones, sweeping through underground streams and bypassing traps, you get to this house. Suddenly you see a silhouette in the window, it moves toward the door. The door creaks open and a long black beard peeps in from behind the door, inlaid with a rare gray hair. The wrinkled face of a hunchbacked grandfather stares at you, screwing up his eyes and changing his face asks: \"Who the hell are you?\"\n- Uh, hello, sir, I'm a pirate and a traveler, some people who have sailed on frigates are hunting for me. I saw this cave in the distance and decided to hide here, later I found this card, which brought me here\n- Is there gold?\n“Most of it is on my ship, but I also have a bit with me.\nCome in, the black-bearded sire wheezed. The house of this tramp was almost empty, the only thing that was here besides the old man was a bed with three legs and a few bottles of kom. You would not mind k